This article is a transcript of President Joe Biden's remarks during his visit to Somerset County, New Jersey, following the devastation caused by Hurricane Ida. He expressed gratitude to local officials, first responders, and FEMA for their efforts in responding to the disaster. Biden emphasized the need to address climate change and build back better to prevent future damage from extreme weather events. He also mentioned the ongoing assessments and assistance being provided by FEMA to affected communities. Other speakers at the event included FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, Somerset County Commissioner Director Shanel Robinson, and New Jersey State Police Superintendent Colonel Pat Callahan. They discussed the scale of the damage, the need for resilience and preparedness, and the ongoing recovery efforts.